Society's Hand:

You look upon the world
and dare you see it's true colors?
Mindless slave
do walk in colored clothing,
out casts
do walk in darkened clothes;
no warm soft light
to warm my thoughts,
no hells fire
to hot to burn.
No world so perfect
no life to lead;
when all is lost
your only a pawn
to die unfairly
in society's hand.

It's easy to cast your fears away behind a mask, a mask in which no one can seem to see through only you. I hold it in as I hide behind the  mask of joy as my parents praise me as a jojyful daughter; all the the while you knew I hurt. You saw the teares even w hen I held them in my bright hazel eyes, you saw my frown hidden away behind my fake smile. I could fool anyone and everyone, everyone but you dear love that sees right trough me. So much pain  I have barried away and all you'll see is a empty shell. I have lived a lie so long, oh how you blood hell knew that lie. No more, here is my true side, no more the fake smile but the true frown; no more the bright eyes they look dead with tears. No longer the angel of lifes, but now the angel of truth and pure inner damnnation.

Suicide:

Day by day
a pondering thought runs,
runs through my broken mind.
A mind so dazed
not even death could render it.
A loaded pistol
in a shaking  hand;
it's over.
No more people 
to laugh,
their laugh dead.
No more tears 
to cry,
the tears run dry.
A bloody mess
to hide the sin
of a dance in fire.

A Soldier

He is that fallen lance that lies as hurled,
That lies unlifted now, come dew, come rust,
But still lies pointed as it ploughed the dust.
If we who sight along it round the world,
See nothing worthy to have been its mark,
It is because like men we look too near,
Forgetting that as fitted to the sphere,
Our missiles always make too short an arc.
They fall, they rip the grass, they intersect
The curve of earth, and striking, break their own;
They make us cringe for metal-point on stone.
But this we know, the obstacle that checked
And tripped the body, shot the spirit on
Further than target ever showed or shone.
